      "0x2409af0251dcb89ee3dee572629291f9b087c668/contracts/protocol/lendingpool/LendingPool.sol:861"
    ],
    "claim": "AaveOracle stores an arbitrary Chainlink aggregator per asset and returns latestAnswer() verbatim, but it never reads aggregator.decimals() or scales the answer to BASE_CURRENCY_UNIT. All downstream collateral, borrow, and liquidation math assumes the returned price is already normalized.",
    "impact": "A single feed configured with the wrong decimals misprices the reserve by orders of magnitude. An overvalued collateral feed lets attackers overborrow and drain other reserves; an undervalued debt/collateral feed can trigger wrongful liquidations or freeze healthy positions.",
    "paths": [
      "An asset source is configured with an 8-dec or otherwise non-normalized feed",
      "Users deposit the overvalued asset as collateral",
      "Borrow limits are computed from the inflated oracle value and correctly priced reserves can be drained"
    ]
  },
