    ],
    "claim": "Although the aggregator interface exposes latestTimestamp/round data, the oracle only reads latestAnswer() and accepts any positive value forever. No heartbeat, updatedAt, round-completeness, or answered-in-round validation is enforced before the value is used in solvency checks.",
    "impact": "During oracle outages or delayed updates, borrowers can keep using stale-high collateral prices or stale-low debt prices to avoid liquidation and extract underpriced liquidity. The protocol stays exposed until governance/operator intervention rather than failing closed on bad oracle data.",
    "paths": [
      "A feed stops updating but continues returning its last positive answer",
      "Collateral or debt keeps being valued at the stale price inside GenericLogic.calculateUserAccountData",
      "Attackers borrow or avoid liquidation against obsolete market conditions"
    ]
