    "claim": "Deposits, repayments, liquidation repayments, flash-loan repayments, and aToken burns all assume the requested amount moved exactly. The code updates rates, mints/burns accounting, and clears debt using the nominal amount parameter, but never reconciles against the token balance delta actually received/transferred.",
    "impact": "If a listed reserve token is fee-on-transfer, rebasing, or otherwise non-standard, attackers can receive too many aTokens for too little underlying, erase debt while sending less value to the pool, or under-repay flash loans. That creates immediate insolvency against standard reserves.",
    "paths": [
