    "claim": "The reserve config explicitly allows decimals up to 255, but core borrow/account/liquidation/swap formulas repeatedly compute 10**decimals. In Solidity 0.6, exponentiation above 77 overflows uint256 and reverts.",
    "impact": "Listing a token with 78-255 decimals can brick borrowing, health-factor calculation, liquidation math, and adapter swaps for that market. Positions can become unmanageable or permanently stuck because critical code paths revert instead of handling the asset safely.",
    "paths": [
